body.p:
To hide the TOC you have two options:

Use a DITA bookmap  instead of a DITA map, and omit  the toc
          element from the booklists. An example bookmap can be found in the  DITA 1.3 Spec. This is the better approach.

Use a display:none to hide the element that contains the TOC structure,
          and also remove it from the PDF bookmarks
          tree:*[class ~= "map/map"] > *[class ~= "toc/toc"] {
  display:none;
}

*[class ~= "map/map"] > *[class ~= "toc/toc"] > *[class ~= "toc/title"]{
  bookmark-label: none;	
  -ah-bookmark-label: none;
}
